						<summary>

						<p>On a granite pillar set up in front of the Śiva temple on the bank of the Kṛishṇā.</p>						

						<p>Seems to register the gift of incomes at the wharf of Ēlīśvaram from the villages, Gummalam, Krottalūru, Eyipūru etc., for offerings and worship to the god Ēlēśvara by Chāḷukya Tribhuvanamalla Mallideva.</p>						

